Explicitly pass `&block` to `Proc.new`

Without this, `ruby examples/call/call.rb` fails with `tried to create Proc object without a block (ArgumentError)`.

commit.message:
customize which signals are sent to stop process

User can now optionially set which signals are sent in which order.
eg `--signals_and_waits=TERM:10|KILL:20` is sending TERM and waiting 10s, then sending KILL and waiting 20s
